WHO   — Maggie Skolnik — the mother · checked-out, adulterous
WHAT  — The suburban update of Dostoevsky's broken families: a parent too lost in her own escape to see her daughter's danger.
WHERE — CPS · Crime + Punishment in Suburbia  Framework inputs: Crime + Punishment in Suburbia (2000)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the film grounds its tragedy in ordinary suburban neglect — the adults looking away while the worst happens.
HOW   — By an affair, denial, and the practiced not-seeing that lets the abuse continue.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I looked everywhere but at my own daughter — the suburb's real crime is how easily the grown-ups learn not to see.

